So I was asked recently whether I’m afraid living in a house with 3 pitbulls. You would think I would shudder at this, being a pitbull advocate, but it’s actually my favorite question! The answer is no: the nervousness about living alone, my anxiety, the day’s stress: they all melt away when I come home to my girls every night. I’m not afraid of them; I’m not afraid because of them! ❤️

Homeland’s Nick Brody needs a home(land)! Nick is a 5-6 year old Hound/Shepherd mix (though, one look at his ears and you might think he’s part bat!). He’s a big goofball who’s very happy to play and run around, but, he’s also always excited to snuggle and show affection to his humans. Brody loves balls, but if you really want to impress him, antlers are his absolute favorite treat. This fun-loving pup has manners to spare and knows all sorts of tricks: he’s housebroken, crate trained, and he’ll sit, lie down, shake and go to place if you just say the words. All you have to say first is, “Come home with me, Nick Brody!" Nick Brody is neutered, up to date on vaccines, and microchipped. Email seespotrescued@gmail.com for an adoption application. #SSRNickBrody .
